11. Additional Documents. In addition to this Construction Contract, this transaction shall
be evidenced by the following additional documents, all of which have been executed
on or before the date of this Construction Contract:
Note from Owner to Lender described in Section 4.
Deed of Trust from Owner to Lender, described in Section 5.
Construction Loan Agreement between Owner and Lender and acknowledged by
(Optional with Owner and Contractor) Additional agreements between Owner and
Contractor, such as "AIA Documents A107" or such other agreements between
Owner and Contractor as they may agree, so long as the terms of such documents
do not conflict with the terms of this document, the Note, the Deed of Trust or the
Construction Loan Agreement.
12. No Work Commenced. (This Construction Contract is executed, acknowledged, and
delivered before any tabor, has been performed and before any material has been
furnished for the construction of the improvements. Owner and Contractor agree to
indemnify and save harmless- Lender from any claims of any artisan, laborer,
mechanic, materialman, subcontractor or supplier which may arise as a result of the
construction of the improvements, and Owner and Contractor agree to pay off and
obtain the discharge of such claims and assure that no liens will be asserted against the
real property hereinabove described,
NOTICE
"IMPORTANT NOTICE: YOU AND YOUR CONTRACTOR ARE RESPONSIBLE
FOR MEETING THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF THIS CONTRACT. IF YOU SIGN THIS
CONTRACT AND YOU FAIL TO MEET THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF THIS
CONTRACT, YOU MAY LOSE YOUR LEGAL\OWNERSHIP RIGHTS IN YOUR HOME.
KNOW YOUR RIGHTS AND DUTIES UNDER THE LAWS
This contract is subject to Chapter 27 of the Texas Property Code, The provisions of that
chapter may affect your right to recover damages arising from a construction defect. If you
have a complaint concerning a construction defect and that defect has not been corrected as
may be required by law or contract, you must provide notice regarding the defect to the
contractor by certified mail, return receipt requested, not later than-the sixtieth day before
the date you file suit to recover damages in a court of law, or initiate arbitration. The notice
must refer to Chapter 27 of the Texas Property Code and must describe-the construction
defect. If requested by the contractor, you must provide the contractor an opportunity to
inspect and cure the defect as provided by Section 27.004 of the Texas Property Code.
